definitions: Past tense of strain: to make a strenuous effort.
Past tense of strain: to injure a muscle or part of the body by overexertion.
Past tense of strain: to filter a liquid or separate solids from a liquid.
Past tense of strain: to stretch or pull something tight.
examples: He strained to lift the heavy box.
She strained her back while gardening.
The rope strained under the weight.
